## Pasteable prompt for Claude Code (senior→senior)

Use this as your Claude Code task prompt:

```text
You are a senior engineer. Implement Project A: a hardened webhook notification receiver for macOS.

Context
- I want a single notification “hub” for coding agents (Claude Code hooks) and other automation.
- MVP: sound-only “ping” on my Mac when an authenticated webhook arrives.
- Stretch: different sounds per source (2–10 sources).
- The service will be exposed publicly via a tunnel (e.g., Tailscale Funnel), so assume random internet traffic; bind the server only to 127.0.0.1.

Deliverables
1) notify-server daemon (macOS) listening on 127.0.0.1:8666 by default.
2) notify-send CLI wrapper for use in hooks; reads secrets from env (NOT committed to repo).
3) launchd LaunchAgent plist to start/keep server alive on login.
4) README with setup, security model, tunnel notes, key rotation, troubleshooting.
5) Unit tests for auth + replay + size + source mismatch + rate limiting.

Technical requirements (must)
- Endpoint: POST /notify
- Headers required:
  - X-Key-Id
  - X-Timestamp (unix seconds)
  - X-Signature = base64(HMAC-SHA256(secret, "<timestamp>.<raw_body>"))
- Body JSON required: { "source": string, "message": string }
  Optional fields accepted: event, repo, context_id, severity, meta (ignored for MVP but accepted)
- Verify: source == X-Key-Id
- Replay resistance: reject if abs(now - timestamp) > 60s (configurable)
- Constant-time signature compare
- Body size limit: default 4096 bytes (configurable)
- Rate limit: token bucket per key-id, default 10/min burst 3 (configurable)
- Do not ever execute arbitrary commands or accept a sound path from request body.
  Sound selection is strictly server-configured per source.
- Play sound with afplay using argv array (no shell=True)
- Logging: do not log secrets/signatures or full payload; log outcomes + key-id + message length.
- Return codes:
  - 204 success
  - 401 auth/replay/source mismatch
  - 413 too large
  - 429 rate limited
  - 400 invalid JSON

Config
- Use a config file in user home (JSON or YAML) that includes:
  - listen_addr, max_body_bytes, max_skew_seconds, rate_limit_per_minute, rate_limit_burst
  - senders map: key-id -> { secrets: [..] (support multiple for rotation), sound: "/path/file" }
  - default_sound fallback
- Server should refuse to start if config missing/invalid (fail closed) OR start denying all requests; choose one and document.

Implementation choice
- Prefer a single Go binary (net/http) to minimize dependencies, unless you have a strong reason to use Python.
- If Go: include a small internal HMAC verifier, JSON parsing, token bucket limiter, and afplay invocation.
- If Python: keep deps minimal and document install; still must be launchd-friendly.

Hook integration
- notify-send should accept CLI args like:
  --source, --message, --event, --repo, --context-id, --severity
  It should compute headers and POST to NOTIFY_URL.
- Secrets come from env: NOTIFY_KEY_ID, NOTIFY_SECRET (or per-source env), or from a local config file outside repos.
- Provide example snippet for Claude Code hooks that calls notify-send.

Docs
- Include quickstart:
  - install/build
  - create config
  - run server
  - local curl test + notify-send test
  - launchd install/enable
  - tunnel exposure notes (public endpoint hits localhost)

Do the work in a clean repo structure:
- server/, client/, launchd/, examples/, README.md, tests/
- Keep code readable and production-grade; handle errors carefully.
- Provide a final checklist verifying acceptance criteria.
```

